# Branch workflow

- **Default work branch:** do day-to-day work on `develop` (locally: `git checkout develop` and pull before editing).
- **`main`** is the release / production integration branch. Do not push commits directly to `main`.
- **Pull requests into `main`:** only from `develop` (see `.github/workflows/merge-to-main-guard.yml`). Do not open PRs from `feature/…`, `fix/…`, or other head branches **into** `main`.
- **Feature and fix work:** use short-lived branches **from** `develop` and open PRs **into** `develop` (or commit directly to `develop` if your team allows it). When `develop` is ready, open **one** PR `develop` → `main` (or merge it through your release process on GitHub that uses that same pair of branches).
- In GitHub **Settings → Branches** (or **Rules** / rulesets) for `main`, mark the `develop → main only` check as **required** so the branch policy cannot be merged around.
- Automation (e.g. Dependabot) that opens PRs into `main` from other head branches will fail the guard until those tools are set to use `target-branch: develop` or a documented exception is added in the guard workflow.
- `git config init.defaultBranch develop` is optional for new local repos; the remote default branch is configured on GitHub.
